  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Combine your <strong>chipotle paste</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong>tomato paste </strong>in a bowl<strong> </strong>– this is your <strong>spiced tomato paste</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-4-1649169495620-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-4-1649169495620-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-4-1649169495620-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-4-1649169495620-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-4-1649169495620-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>spiced tomato paste</strong> to the pan with 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[225ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> and season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Cover with a lid and cook for an initial 7-10 min or until the sauce has reduced slightly</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-4-1649169503275-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-4-1649169503275-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-4-1649169503275-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-4-1649169503275-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-4-1649169503275-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>hake fillets </strong>into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Sprinkle your <strong>ground</strong> <strong>cumin</strong>, <strong>ground</strong> <strong>coriander</strong> and a large pinch of <strong>salt </strong>over the <strong>chopped hake </strong>and gently rub the spices all over the fish</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-copy-4-1649169514190-x200.jpg",
